# Design System Rules

## Source Of Truth

- MUST use tokens from `@src/client/styles/base/variables.css` for colors, typography, spacing, radius, and timing.
- MUST prefer UI primitives from `@src/client/components/ui/` before introducing feature-level variants.
- SHOULD align visual behavior with proven patterns from:
  - `@src/client/pages/PublicationPage.tsx` and `@src/client/pages/PublicationPage.css`
  - `@src/client/components/ReadingMode/index.tsx` and `@src/client/components/ReadingMode/ReadingMode.css`

## Design Tokens

- MUST avoid new hardcoded color values (`#...`, `rgb(...)`) in component CSS when an existing token can be used.
- MUST avoid ad-hoc spacing and radius values when token equivalents exist.
- MUST use responsive tokens and layout variables from `@src/client/styles/base/variables.css` before adding new breakpoint constants.
- SHOULD keep shadow intensity and border contrast consistent with `Button.css`, `Modal.css`, and publication card patterns.
- SHOULD prefer semantic tokens (`--text-secondary`, `--bg-card`, `--border-hover`) over one-off visual tweaks.

## Typography

- MUST use the existing type scale from `variables.css` (`--text-*`) for body, labels, helper text, and headings.
- MUST preserve clear hierarchy: primary headings (`--text-primary` + stronger weight), supportive metadata (`--text-dim`).
- SHOULD use readable line-height for text-heavy blocks (especially reader and modal content).
- SHOULD avoid introducing non-system font families for UI controls.

## Buttons

- MUST use `Button` from `@src/client/components/ui/Button.tsx` for generic actions.
- MUST preserve accessible targets (minimum `44x44` for touchable controls, except intentionally compact desktop-only controls).
- MUST support consistent states: default, hover, focus-visible, disabled, loading.
- SHOULD use:
  - `primary` for main CTA on a view.
  - `secondary` for neutral/less prominent actions.
  - dedicated destructive styles only for irreversible actions.
- SHOULD avoid inline-styled button visuals in feature components.

## Back Navigation Pattern

- MUST keep back actions visually consistent across pages and reading contexts.
- SHOULD use a shared back button style/pattern (arrow + short localized label), with visible focus state.
- SHOULD avoid creating new one-off back button classes unless there is a strong layout constraint.

## Modals

- MUST use `Modal` from `@src/client/components/ui/Modal.tsx` for standard overlays.
- MUST keep consistent structure: header, content/body, action footer.
- MUST support close behavior through Escape and backdrop click unless flow explicitly blocks closing.
- MUST keep keyboard and focus-visible access usable for close/action controls.
- SHOULD keep modal sizing and spacing aligned with existing modal breakpoints and token spacing.

## Icons

- MUST keep icon usage consistent in size and alignment within the same control family.
- SHOULD prefer one visual style per area (same perceived weight and interaction affordance).
- MUST provide accessible names (`aria-label`/title/context) for icon-only controls.
- SHOULD avoid mixing many icon metaphors in one toolbar.
- MUST use Google Material Symbols via `@src/client/components/ui/Icon.tsx` for control icons.
- MUST NOT introduce emoji as control icons when an equivalent Material Symbol exists.
- MAY use emoji only for explicitly decorative, non-interactive content states.
- MUST track icon mapping and allowed decorative exceptions in `@docs/ICONS_PLAN.md`.

## Cards And Lists

- MUST keep card/list behavior consistent: border + subtle elevation + clear hover/active/read states.
- SHOULD reuse existing publication/project card patterns rather than creating new card systems.
- MUST keep list item actions aligned and preserve readable truncation behavior for long titles.

## Forms

- MUST use shared `Input`/`Select`/`Slider` primitives where possible.
- MUST include clear states: default, focus, error, disabled.
- SHOULD keep labels, helper text, and validation messages visually consistent and localized.
- SHOULD avoid inline styles for form controls.

## Loading, Empty, Error States

- MUST show deterministic loading state for async content (`LoadingSpinner` or equivalent standard pattern).
- MUST provide clear empty/error copy with an obvious recovery action when possible.
- SHOULD keep these states visually calm and consistent with page tone.

## Accessibility And Motion

- MUST preserve keyboard navigation for interactive UI and modal flows.
- MUST keep visible `:focus-visible` styles on controls.
- SHOULD maintain WCAG-friendly contrast for text and controls.
- SHOULD avoid excessive motion; keep transitions short and purpose-driven.

## Responsive (Mobile First)

- MUST design and verify UI in order: mobile -> tablet -> desktop.
- MUST check each changed screen/component on at least 3 viewport classes (mobile, tablet, desktop).
- MUST keep touch targets >= 44px for interactive controls on mobile/tablet.
- MUST avoid horizontal scrolling and clipped actions with long localized strings.
- SHOULD keep modal, back-button, and toolbar behavior visually consistent on narrow screens.
- SHOULD keep inline styles only for runtime geometry (for example virtualization or measured offsets).

## i18n UI Copy

- MUST avoid hardcoded UI strings in client components; use `useTranslation()` and locale keys.
- MUST add new keys to all locale files: `src/client/locales/en.json`, `src/client/locales/ru.json`, `src/client/locales/pl.json`.
- SHOULD keep CTA labels short and action-oriented.

## Implementation Checklist For UI Changes

- Tokens used (no unnecessary hardcoded colors/sizes).
- Existing UI primitives reused before custom components.
- States covered (hover/focus-visible/disabled/loading where applicable).
- Keyboard + focus-visible verified for interactive controls.
- i18n keys added for all user-facing text.
- Responsive verified on mobile/tablet/desktop without layout breaks.
